.TH "batadv_neigh_node_get" 9 "batadv_neigh_node_get" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
batadv_neigh_node_get \- retrieve a neighbour from the list
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct batadv_neigh_node *" batadv_neigh_node_get
.BI "(const struct batadv_orig_node *orig_node "  ","
.BI "const struct batadv_hard_iface *hard_iface "  ","
.BI "const u8 *addr "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "orig_node" 12
originator which the neighbour belongs to
.IP "hard_iface" 12
the interface where this neighbour is connected to
.IP "addr" 12
the address of the neighbour
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Looks for and possibly returns a neighbour belonging to this originator list
which is connected through the provided hard interface.
.SH "RETURN"
neighbor when found. Otherwise NULL
